  "doc_id": "21991",
  "text": "Anti-Fu1a is a mouse monoclonal antibody specific for NDV F protein and was obtained from M. Peeples. Anti-HR1 and anti-HR2 antibodies were raised against peptides with sequences from the NDV F protein HR1 and HR2 domains, respectively, and have been previously described [CITATION_1] . Anti-AS antibody was raised against the peptide encoded between the AluI to SmaI sites in the HN DNA (corresponding to amino acids 115 to 515) from the NDV HN protein and has been previously described [CITATION_2] . Anti-NDV antibody was raised in rabbits against UV-inactivated stocks of NDV, strain AV, by standard protocols as previously described [CITATION_3] . Mouse monoclonal anti-PDI and anti-ERdj5 antibodies were purchased from Abnova Corporation.",
